<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="97">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:230099" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Polyrhachis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Polyrhachis (Campomyrma) micans subsp. ops var. rufa" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="micans" subGenus="Campomyrma" subSpecies="ops" variety="rufa">Polyrhachis (Campomyrma) micans, Mayr., race ops, Forel, var. rufa</taxonomicName>
, nov.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="97">
[[worker]]. Differs from 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34964" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Polyrhachis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Polyrhachis micans Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micans">micans</taxonomicName>
in colour, which is black, with the mandibles, clypeus, frontal area, anterior portion of frontal carinae, cheeks at base of mandibles, antennae, legs, scale, and gaster light red. The upper portion of the declivity of epinotum below the teeth and the teeth themselves are red, but not so bright as the other red portions.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="97">
Thorax formed like that of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:143375" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Polyrhachis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Polyrhachis micans subsp. ops Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="micans" subSpecies="ops">race ops</taxonomicName>
- i. e.t narrower than in 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34964" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Polyrhachis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Polyrhachis micans Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micans">micans</taxonomicName>
; the anterior border of clypeus not so deeply concave and the teeth not so prominent as in 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34964" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Polyrhachis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Polyrhachis micans Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micans">micans</taxonomicName>
. The teeth on epinotum much shorter and blunter than in 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34964" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Polyrhachis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Polyrhachis micans Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micans">micans</taxonomicName>
, and the inner spines on the scale are somewhat shorter and more parallel, while the lateral spines are reduced to mere triangular teeth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="97">
This variety would appear to differ from the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:230098" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Polyrhachis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Polyrhachis micans var. dentinasis" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="micans" variety="dentinasis">var. dentinasis</taxonomicName>
recently described by Santschi by its red colour and the even greater diminution of the lateral spines of the scale.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
